Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.hashtable

Class HashTable_SC<Key,Value>

java.lang.Object
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.hashtable.HashTable_SC<Key,Value>
Type Parameters:
Key - the type of keys maintained by this hash table.
Value - the type of mapped values.
All Implemented Interfaces:
ImmutableSymbolTable<Key,Value>, ST<Key,Value>
public class HashTable_SC<Key,Value> extends Object
HashTable_SC is a hash table implementation using separate chaining (SC) for collision resolution. This class supports basic operations such as insertion, retrieval, and key set generation. It also implements the ST interface for working with key-value pairs.

  • Field Details

    • m

      protected final int m
      The size of the array in this hash table. This determines the capacity of the hash table and plays a key role in distributing the keys across the buckets to minimize collisions. The value of m is constant and initialized at the time of constructing the HashTable instance.

    • findKeyValuePair

      protected Optional<com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.hashtable.HashTable.KeyValuePair<Key,Value>> findKeyValuePair(Key key, int index)
      Finds and retrieves the key-value pair associated with the specified key by searching in the bucket at the given index. It first finds the appropriate Node using findNodeByKey. If a matching key exists, the corresponding key-value pair is returned wrapped in an Optional.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose associated key-value pair needs to be found.
      index - the index of the bucket in which to search for the key.
      Returns:
      an Optional containing the key-value pair if found, or an empty Optional if no match exists.

    • findNodeByKey

      @NotNull protected <Element> Optional<Element> findNodeByKey(Key key, int index)
      Finds and retrieves the first node matching the specified key within the bucket at the given index. The method searches the bucket for nodes whose key matches the provided key and ensures there is at most one match. If multiple matches are found, an exception is thrown. If no match is found, an empty Optional is returned.
      Type Parameters:
      Element - the type of the element to be returned, inferred from the caller's context.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to search for in the specified bucket.
      index - the index of the bucket within the hash table where the search will be performed.
      Returns:
      an Optional containing the matching node if found, or an empty Optional if no match exists.
